Once you have searched the catalogue, you can use the Processing API to download imagery directly, then upload it to S3 so it can be shared with your team. The SSP Cloud provides an S3-compatible object store accessible via s3fs. Here is how to initialise an S3FileSystem and upload a file:

from utils import get_file_system

fs = get_file_system()

# Upload a local file to S3
fs.put("./output.tif", "s3://my-bucket/sentinel2/output.tif")







